---
import SectionHeader from '../ui/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<section class="section-padding-lg bg-bronze-900/60 text-parchment">
    <div class="container-content">
        <div class="grid items-start gap-12 lg:grid-cols-12 lg:gap-20">
            <div class="space-y-6 lg:sticky lg:top-28 lg:col-span-5">
                <SectionHeader
                    label="Philosophy"
                    title="Islam as a framework for living well"
                    dark={true}
                />
                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-parchment-200">
                    We write for men who refuse to treat dunya and deen as rivals. Your body, your
                    character, your family, your work, and your worship are not competing priorities
                    — they are parts of one life, and neglecting any of them weakens the whole.
                </p>
                <p class="leading-relaxed text-parchment-300">
                    The modern world offers endless distraction and comfort. Our standard is different:
                    slow, deliberate growth through habits, knowledge, and responsibility — measured
                    in years, not viral moments.
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 border-l-2 border-gold/30 pl-5 text-sm text-parchment-300">
                    <li>Faith as orientation, not decoration</li>
                    <li>Discipline as daily practice, not motivation</li>
                    <li>Knowledge applied, not merely collected</li>
                    <li>Strength in service of others, not self-image</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-8 lg:col-span-7">
                <p class="text-justify text-lg leading-relaxed text-parchment-200 sm:text-xl">
                    Islam is not only a set of rituals. It is a complete framework for living
                    responsibly, purposefully, and effectively in the modern world.
                </p>
                <p class="text-justify leading-relaxed text-parchment-300">
                    The Capable Muslim exists because too many men treat faith and worldly
                    competence as separate pursuits — as if salah and strength, character and
                    career, discipline and deen have nothing to do with each other. They do.
                    Everything connects.
                </p>
                <p class="text-justify leading-relaxed text-parchment-300">
                    We believe a Muslim man should be healthy enough to serve, disciplined enough
                    to persist, skilled enough to provide, wise enough to lead, and grounded enough
                    in his faith to stay oriented when life gets difficult.
                </p>
                <p class="text-justify leading-relaxed text-parchment-300">
                    This is not about perfection. It is about direction — choosing standards,
                    building habits, and doing the work over years, not weeks.
                </p>

                <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-gold/50 py-2 pl-6">
                    <p class="font-display text-xl italic leading-snug text-parchment sm:text-2xl">
                        "Capability is not arrogance. It is responsibility — the willingness to
                        become someone others can depend on."
                    </p>
                </blockquote>

                <a href="/about" class="btn-primary inline-flex">Learn our approach</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
